{{infobox religious building
 | name = '''Ono Shrine''' (Ichinomiya)|native_name=大野神社
 | religious_affiliation = {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道}}|image=[[File:Ono-jinja, Ichinomiya.jpg|300px]]
 | address = 1042, Higashi, Ono-gō, Asai-chō, Ichinomiya, Aichi Prefecture
 | location = {{Coord|35|21|10.57|N|136|49|29.83|E|scale:30000_region:JP-23}}
 | enshrined_deities = {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|lt=Hotabebito no Mikoto|lt_ja=誉田別命}}　{{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神}}　{{ill|Tatemizukata no Kami|ja|建水方神}}
 | status = Shikinaisha・Former Village Shrine
 | foundation = Unknown
}}

'''Ono Shrine''' (大野神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}}, {{ill|Ichinomiya|ja|一宮市}}, {{ill|Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|ja|浅井町 (愛知県)|lt=Asai Town|lt_ja=浅井町}}. Its former {{ill|Shrine Status|ja|社格}} was that of a Village Shrine. It is situated to the south of {{ill|Ono Gokurakuji Park|ja|大野極楽寺公園}} and beside the {{ill|Morio Embankment|ja|御囲堤}}.

It is the "Ono Shrine" of the {{ill|Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|ja|延喜式神名帳|lt=Shikinai-sha|lt_ja=式内社}} in {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国}}, {{ill|Haguri District|ja|葉栗郡}}.

== Overview ==
* The date of foundation is unknown. It is said that the original location was slightly to the south of the current site.
* It is believed that this was originally a shrine associated with water. Before the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}, due to the enshrinement of {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|lt=Hotabebito no Mikoto|lt_ja=誉田別命}}, it was renamed as a Hachiman Shrine, but in {{ill|1870|ja|1870年}} (the 3rd year of Meiji) it was renamed Ono Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now house the Ono Community Center. Within the precincts, various stone statues (including {{ill|Divine Statue|ja|神像}} and {{ill|Buddhist Statue|ja|仏像}}) and stone monuments—presumed to have once been enshrined—are scattered about.

== Worshipped Deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神}}}}
; Principal Deities
:* {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|lt=Hotabebito no Mikoto|lt_ja=誉田別命}}
:* {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神}}
:* {{ill|Tatemizukata no Kami|ja|建水方神}} (believed to be the same as {{ill|Tatemikata no Kami|ja|建御名方神}})
; Co-Enshrined
:* {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道真}}

== Transportation ==
* Get off at the "Ono" bus stop of the {{ill|Meitetsu Bus|ja|名鉄バス}} and walk for 3 minutes.
** From {{ill|Meitetsu|ja|名鉄}}’s {{ill|Nagoya Main Line|ja|名鉄名古屋本線}} and {{ill|Meitetsu Onishi Line|ja|名鉄尾西線}} at {{ill|Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station|ja|名鉄一宮駅}}, or from the {{ill|Tōkaidō Main Line|ja|Tōkaidō Main Line}} at {{ill|Owari Ichinomiya Station|ja|尾張一宮駅}} (Platform 3 at the {{ill|Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station Bus Terminal|ja|名鉄一宮駅バスターミナル}}) for the "Kawashima" bus.

{{shinto-stub}}

