'''Ono Shrine''' (大野神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ichinomiya|ja|一宮市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|ja|浅井町 (愛知県)|lt=Asai Town|lt_ja=浅井町|12=draft}}. Its former {{ill|Shrine Status|ja|社格|12=draft}} was that of a Village Shrine. It is situated to the south of {{ill|Ono Gokurakuji Park|ja|大野極楽寺公園|12=draft}} and beside the {{ill|Morio Embankment|ja|御囲堤|12=draft}}.

It is the "Ono Shrine" of the {{ill|Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|ja|延喜式神名帳|lt=Shikinai-sha|lt_ja=式内社|12=draft}} in {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国|12=draft}}, {{ill|Haguri District|ja|葉栗郡|12=draft}}.

== Overview ==
* The date of foundation is unknown. It is said that the original location was slightly to the south of the current site.
* It is believed that this was originally a shrine associated with water. Before the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|12=draft}}, due to the enshrinement of {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|lt=Hotabebito no Mikoto|lt_ja=誉田別命|12=draft}}, it was renamed as a Hachiman Shrine, but in {{ill|1870|ja|1870th year|12=draft}} (the 3rd year of Meiji) it was renamed Ono Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now house the Ono Community Center. Within the precincts, various stone statues (including {{ill|Divine Statue|ja|神像|12=draft}} and {{ill|Buddhist Statue|ja|仏像|12=draft}}) and stone monuments—presumed to have once been enshrined—are scattered about.

== Worshipped Deities (Saijin) ==
