It is the "Ono Shrine" of the {{ill|Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Shikinai-sha|lt_ja=式内社|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Haguri District|ja|葉栗郡|qq=draft}}.

== Overview ==
* The date of foundation is unknown. It is said that the original location was slightly to the south of the current site.
* It is believed that this was originally a shrine associated with water. Before the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft}}, due to the enshrinement of {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|lt=Hotabebito no Mikoto|lt_ja=誉田別命|qq=draft}}, it was renamed as a Hachiman Shrine, but in {{ill|1870|ja|1870th year|qq=draft}} (the 3rd year of Meiji) it was renamed Ono Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now house the Ono Community Center. Within the precincts, various stone statues (including {{ill|Divine Statue|ja|神像|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Buddhist Statue|ja|仏像|qq=draft}}) and stone monuments—presumed to have once been enshrined—are scattered about.

== Worshipped Deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|qq=draft}}}}
; Principal Deities
:* {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|lt=Hotabebito no Mikoto|lt_ja=誉田別命|qq=draft}}
:* {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qq=draft}}
:* {{ill|Tatemizukata no Kami|ja|建水方神|qq=draft}} (believed to be the same as {{ill|Tatemikata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft}})
; Co-Enshrined
:* {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道真|qq=draft}}

== Transportation ==
* Get off at the "Ono" bus stop of the {{ill|Meitetsu Bus|ja|名鉄バス|qq=draft}} and walk for 3 minutes.
** From {{ill|Meitetsu|ja|名鉄|qq=draft}}’s {{ill|Nagoya Main Line|ja|名鉄名古屋本線|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Meitetsu Onishi Line|ja|名鉄尾西線|qq=draft}} at {{ill|Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station|ja|名鉄一宮駅|qq=draft}}, or from the {{ill|Tōkaidō Main Line|ja|Tōkaidō Main Line|qq=draft}} at {{ill|Owari Ichinomiya Station|ja|尾張一宮駅|qq=draft}} (Platform 3 at the {{ill|Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station Bus Terminal|ja|名鉄一宮駅バスターミナル|qq=draft}}) for the "Kawashima" bus.

