'''Ono Shrine''' (大野神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] located in [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]], [[:en:Ichinomiya, Aichi|Ichinomiya]], {{ill|Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|ja|浅井町 (愛知県)|lt=Asai Town|lt_ja=浅井町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|qq=|1=Azai|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11556970}}. Its former {{ill|Shrine Status|ja|社格|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine Status|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=shrine rank|WD=Q10444029}} was that of a Village Shrine. It is situated to the south of {{ill|Ono Gokurakuji Park|ja|大野極楽寺公園|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Gokurakuji Park|qq=|1=Onogokurakuji Park|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11439660}} and beside the {{ill|Morio Embankment|ja|御囲堤|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Morio Embankment|qq=|1=Morio Embankment|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11488847}}.

It is the "Ono Shrine" of the {{ill|Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt=Shikinaisha|lt_ja=式内社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} in [[:en:Owari Province|Owari Province]], [[:en:Haguri District|Haguri District]].

== Overview ==
* The date of foundation is unknown. It is said that the original location was slightly to the south of the current site.
* It is believed that this was originally a shrine associated with water. Before the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], due to the enshrinement of [[:en:Hachiman|Hotabebito no Mikoto]], it was renamed as a Hachiman Shrine, but in [[:en:1870|1870]] (the 3rd year of Meiji) it was renamed Ono Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now house the Ono Community Center. Within the precincts, various stone statues (including {{ill|Divine Statue|ja|神像|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Statue|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=shinzō|WD=Q11588751}} and [[:en:Buddha in art|Buddhist Statue]]) and stone monuments—presumed to have once been enshrined—are scattered about.

== Worshipped Deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saijin|qq=}}}}
; Principal Deities
:* [[:en:Hachiman|Hotabebito no Mikoto]]
:* [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]]
:* {{ill|Tatemizukata no Kami|ja|建水方神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tatemizukata no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (believed to be the same as [[:en:Takeminakata|Takeminakata]])
; Co-Enshrined
:* [[:en:Sugawara no Michizane|Sugawara no Michizane]]

== Transportation ==
* Get off at the "Ono" bus stop of the [[:en:Meitetsu Bus|Meitetsu Bus]] and walk for 3 minutes.
** From {{ill|Meitetsu|ja|名鉄|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meitetsu|qq=|1=Meitetsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11415661}}’s [[:en:Meitetsu Nagoya Main Line|Nagoya Main Line]] and [[:en:Meitetsu Bisai Line|Meitetsu Onishi Line]] at [[:en:Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station|Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station]], or from the {{ill|Tōkaidō Main Line|ja|Tōkaidō Main Line|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōkaidō Main Line|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} at [[:en:Owari-Ichinomiya Station|Owari Ichinomiya Station]] (Platform 3 at the {{ill|Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station Bus Terminal|ja|名鉄一宮駅バスターミナル|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station Bus Terminal|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 一宮駅バスターミナル|1=Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station Bus Terminal|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11415757}}) for the "Kawashima" bus.

