'''Ono Shrine''' (大野神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] located in [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]], [[:en:Ichinomiya, Aichi|Ichinomiya]], {{ill|Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|ja|浅井町 (愛知県)|lt=Asai Town|lt_ja=浅井町|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|1=Azai|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11556970}}. Its former {{ill|Shrine Status|ja|社格|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine Status|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=shrine rank|WD=Q10444029}} was that of a Village Shrine. It is situated to the south of {{ill|Ono Gokurakuji Park|ja|大野極楽寺公園|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Gokurakuji Park|1=Onogokurakuji Park|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11439660}} and beside the {{ill|Morio Embankment|ja|御囲堤|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Morio Embankment|1=Morio Embankment|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11488847}}.

It is the "Ono Shrine" of the {{ill|Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt=Shikinaisha|lt_ja=式内社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} in [[:en:Owari Province|Owari Province]], [[:en:Haguri District|Haguri District]].

== Overview ==
* The date of foundation is unknown. It is said that the original location was slightly to the south of the current site.
* It is believed that this was originally a shrine associated with water. Before the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], due to the enshrinement of [[:en:Hachiman|Hotabebito no Mikoto]], it was renamed as a Hachiman Shrine, but in [[:en:1870|1870]] (the 3rd year of Meiji) it was renamed Ono Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now house the Ono Community Center. Within the precincts, various stone statues (including {{ill|Divine Statue|ja|神像|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Statue|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=shinzō|WD=Q11588751}} and [[:en:Buddha in art|Buddhist Statue]]) and stone monuments—presumed to have once been enshrined—are scattered about.

