'''Ōno Shrine''' (Ōno-jinja) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in {{jalink|Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|Q11556970|Asai-chō}}, {{jalink|Ichinomiya City|Q270810}}, {{jalink|Aichi Prefecture|Q80434}}. Its former {{jalink|shrine ranking system|Q10444029}} status was that of a village shrine. It is located south of {{jalink|Ōno Gokurakuji Park|Q11439660}}, near the {{jalink|Okakoi embankment|Q11488847}}.

It is listed as the “Ōno Shrine” of {{jalink|Haguri District|Q1032507}}, {{jalink|Owari Province|Q514506}} in the {{jalink|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|Engishiki shrine register}}.<ref>https://jmapps.ne.jp/kokugakuin/det.html?data_id=181383</ref>

=== Overview ===
* The date of establishment is unknown. It is said that the shrine was originally located slightly south of its present site.
* It is said to have originally been a shrine associated with water. Before the {{jalink|Edo period|Q184963}}, after Hondawake no Mikoto was enshrined, it was renamed a Hachiman Shrine; however, in {{jalink|1870|Q7741}} (Meiji 3), it was renamed Ōno Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now serves as the Ōno Community Center. Within the grounds, stone statues ({{jalink|stone statues|Q12573007}}—{{jalink|Shinto deity statues|Q11588751}}, {{jalink|Buddhist statues|Q1000809}}) and stone monuments, presumed to have once been worshipped, exist in a disorderly manner.

=== Enshrined Deities ===
;Main deities
:*{{jalink|Hachiman|Q261637|Hondawake no Mikoto}}
:*{{jalink|Amaterasu Ōmikami|Q455602}}
:*{{jalink|Takemizuwake no Kami}} (presumed to be {{jalink|Takeminakata no Kami}})
;Enshrined together
:*{{jalink|Sugawara no Michizane|Q382005}}

=== Transportation ===
* Get off at the “Ōno” bus stop on {{jalink|Meitetsu Bus|Q6810397}}, then walk 3 minutes.
** From {{jalink|Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station|Q2856589}} on the {{jalink|Nagoya Railroad|Q30850}}{{jalink|Meitetsu Nagoya Main Line|Q1137838|Nagoya Main Line}} / {{jalink|Meitetsu Bisai Line|Q901005|Bisai Line}}, or from {{jalink|Owari-Ichinomiya Station|Q871495}} on the {{jalink|Tōkaidō Main Line|Q1190152}} (Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station Bus Terminal, platform 3), take the bus bound for “Kawashima.”

