* Part of the shrine grounds now serves as the Ōno Community Center. Within the grounds, stone statues ({{jalink|stone statues|Q12573007}}—{{jalink|Shinto deity statues|Q11588751}}, {{jalink|Buddhist statues|Q1000809}}) and stone monuments, presumed to have once been worshipped, exist in a disorderly manner.

