'''Ono Shrine''' (大野神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|Shinto shrine|WD=Q845945|lt=Shinto Shrine}} located in {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|en|Aichi Prefecture|WD=Q80434|lt=Aichi Prefecture}}, {{ill|Ichinomiya, Aichi|en|Ichinomiya, Aichi|WD=Q270810|lt=Ichinomiya}}, {{ill|Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|ja|浅井町 (愛知県)|lt=Asai Town|lt_ja=浅井町|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|1=Azai|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11556970}}. Its former {{ill|Shrine Status|ja|社格|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine Status|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=shrine rank|WD=Q10444029}} was that of a Village Shrine. It is situated to the south of {{ill|Ono Gokurakuji Park|ja|大野極楽寺公園|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Gokurakuji Park|1=Onogokurakuji Park|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11439660}} and beside the {{ill|Morio Embankment|ja|御囲堤|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Morio Embankment|1=Morio Embankment|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11488847}}.

It is the "Ono Shrine" of the {{ill|Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|lt=Shikinaisha|lt_ja=式内社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Warrant of Deities of the Engi Era|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} in {{ill|Owari Province|en|Owari Province|WD=Q514506|lt=Owari Province}}, {{ill|Haguri District|en|Haguri District|WD=Q1032507|lt=Haguri District}}.

== Overview ==
* The date of foundation is unknown. It is said that the original location was slightly to the south of the current site.
* It is believed that this was originally a shrine associated with water. Before the {{ill|Edo period|en|Edo period|WD=Q184963|lt=Edo period}}, due to the enshrinement of {{ill|Hachiman|en|Hachiman|WD=Q261637|lt=Hotabebito no Mikoto}}, it was renamed as a Hachiman Shrine, but in {{ill|1870|en|1870|WD=Q7741|lt=1870}} (the 3rd year of Meiji) it was renamed Ono Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now house the Ono Community Center. Within the precincts, various stone statues (including {{ill|Divine Statue|ja|神像|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Statue|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=shinzō|WD=Q11588751}} and {{ill|Buddha in art|en|Buddha in art|WD=Q1000809|lt=Buddhist Statue}}) and stone monuments—presumed to have once been enshrined—are scattered about.

