'''Ōno Shrine''' (Ōno-jinja) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} located in {{ill|lt=Asai Town (Aichi Prefecture)|Q11556970|WD=Q11556970|lt=Asai-chō}}, {{ill|lt=Ichinomiya City|Q270810|WD=Q270810}}, {{ill|lt=Aichi Prefecture|Q80434|WD=Q80434}}. Its former {{ill|lt=shrine ranking system|Q10444029|WD=Q10444029}} status was that of a village shrine. It is located south of {{ill|lt=Ōno Gokurakuji Park|Q11439660|WD=Q11439660}}, near the {{ill|lt=Okakoi embankment|Q11488847|WD=Q11488847}}.

It is listed as the “Ōno Shrine” of {{ill|lt=Haguri District|Q1032507|WD=Q1032507}}, {{ill|lt=Owari Province|Q514506|WD=Q514506}} in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Engishiki shrine register}}.<ref>https://jmapps.ne.jp/kokugakuin/det.html?data_id=181383</ref>

=== Overview ===
* The date of establishment is unknown. It is said that the shrine was originally located slightly south of its present site.
* It is said to have originally been a shrine associated with water. Before the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963}}, after Hondawake no Mikoto was enshrined, it was renamed a Hachiman Shrine; however, in {{ill|lt=1870|Q7741|WD=Q7741}} (Meiji 3), it was renamed Ōno Shrine.
* Part of the shrine grounds now serves as the Ōno Community Center. Within the grounds, stone statues ({{ill|lt=stone statues|Q12573007|WD=Q12573007}}—{{ill|lt=Shinto deity statues|Q11588751|WD=Q11588751}}, {{ill|lt=Buddhist statues|Q1000809|WD=Q1000809}}) and stone monuments, presumed to have once been worshipped, exist in a disorderly manner.

=== Enshrined Deities ===
;Main deities
:*{{ill|lt=Hachiman|Q261637|WD=Q261637|lt=Hondawake no Mikoto}}
:*{{ill|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|Q455602|WD=Q455602}}
:*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Takemizuwake no Kami|1=UNKNOWN}} (presumed to be {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Takeminakata no Kami|1=UNKNOWN}})
;Enshrined together
:*{{ill|lt=Sugawara no Michizane|Q382005|WD=Q382005}}

=== Transportation ===
* Get off at the “Ōno” bus stop on {{ill|lt=Meitetsu Bus|Q6810397|WD=Q6810397}}, then walk 3 minutes.
** From {{ill|lt=Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station|Q2856589|WD=Q2856589}} on the {{ill|lt=Nagoya Railroad|Q30850|WD=Q30850}}{{ill|lt=Meitetsu Nagoya Main Line|Q1137838|WD=Q1137838|lt=Nagoya Main Line}} / {{ill|lt=Meitetsu Bisai Line|Q901005|WD=Q901005|lt=Bisai Line}}, or from {{ill|lt=Owari-Ichinomiya Station|Q871495|WD=Q871495}} on the {{ill|lt=Tōkaidō Main Line|Q1190152|WD=Q1190152}} (Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station Bus Terminal, platform 3), take the bus bound for “Kawashima.”

